research_municipality_step.notes: Seattle operates under a mayor-council form of government. Bruce Harrell is the current Mayor, elected in 2021 and taking office on January 1, 2022. The Seattle City Council consists of nine members; seven are elected by district, and two are elected citywide (at-large). As of December 2025, Eddie Lin was elected in November 2025 to fill an unexpired term in District 2, and Debora Juarez was appointed in July 2025 to represent District 5 until a special election in 2026. Other elected officials in Seattle include the City Attorney (Ann Davison) and Municipal Court Judges (Faye Chess, Andrea Chin, Anita Crawford-Willis, Willie Gregory, Catherine McDowall, Damon Shadid, and Pooja Vaddadi). While Bruce Harrell is the current mayor, Katie Wilson was reported to have defeated him in the 2025 Seattle mayoral election, indicating a transition for the next term.
